The Cybersecurity Bootcamp at 4Geeks Academy is a 16-week program designed to help individuals become cybersecurity specialists. The program provides a solid foundation in Windows, Linux, network, and server administration, as well as practical skills for securing these environments. Participants will also learn about cloud security, penetration testing, cyber threat intelligence analysis, data loss prevention strategies, and compliance with international standards such as ISO 27001 and NIST. The bootcamp offers 3 live online classes per week, with a maximum class size of 16 people. Upon completion, students will receive an official 4Geeks Completion Certificate. The median annual salary for cybersecurity professionals in the United States is $103,560. For more information, visit the 4Geeks Academy website at https://4geeksacademy.com/us/coding-bootcamps/cybersecurity. stop